From: Paul Gortmaker <paul.gortmaker@windriver.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Jun 2011 16:32:27 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] rt: delete mention of another long gone RT tunable option.

The per-irq tuning variables described in this Kconfig file
no longer exist either.  Remove the mention of them.

Signed-off-by: Paul Gortmaker <paul.gortmaker@windriver.com>

diff --git a/kernel/Kconfig.preempt b/kernel/Kconfig.preempt
index c71c560..6833eeb 100644
--- a/kernel/Kconfig.preempt
+++ b/kernel/Kconfig.preempt
@@ -113,8 +113,6 @@ config PREEMPT_HARDIRQS
           this feature can also reduce performance.
 
           The threading of hardirqs can also be controlled via the
-          hardirq-preempt=0/1 boot-time option. Per-irq threading can
-          be enabled/disable via the /proc/irq/<IRQ>/<handler>/threaded
-          runtime flags.
+          hardirq-preempt=0/1 boot-time option.
 
 	  Say N if you are unsure.
